I’ve been looking lately ”not me” which causes my mood feeling down. I have been only using sweatpants, and washing my hair like once or twice a week. (my hair looked horrible, like cow has been licking it) I did my makeup everyday tho. (and my makeup looked like ”naked rat” as I called it)

But I LOVE DOING MY HAIR (!!) AND MAKEUP and dress nicely. I always have. My best working place was in clothing store which gave me opportunity to do my hair/makeup, put some nice clothes and spend my day with the most awesome ladies, EVERY SINGLE DAY. It was definitely most wonderful time of my life for sure. 

So, now on my vacation, one day I desided to search ”marilyn monroe makeup” on google and recreate it. 

I got my mood lifted instantly. I don’t do hair and makeup ”TO LOOK GOOD”, this is my kind of art. 

Why I love doing hair and makeup?  simply because it’s never ending thing, you can always improve your skills and learn new things. And easiest way to practise this is on your own face/hair. 
Hopefully one day I can do this more on others, than myself. 
(this actually scares me, I don’t know why, but I wanna do it anyway.)
I have seen how much it lifts someones mood when you do makeup/hair for them, and that kind of spirit I want to give to the others. ❤️

Давно прийняла для себе рішення не плодити зайвої косметики і ще одне важливе: закінчувати ту яку маю і не купляти нову:) Нажаль, це не працює з тінями шанель, оскільки вони безкінечні і я думаю давно вже пройшов їх термін. Треба все перевірити по батч коду. Як бачите, в надлишку у мене тільки креми для рук😂😂😂 подарунок адвент календар від @oksanadrapaka вніс свої корективи у момент «ненакопичення» 😅🪷 (улюблений від @philipmartins_ukraine і sisley body теж на руки:), просто неймовірний аромат saffron flowers. I’d like to share my favorite way of applying red lipstick 💄

Since I don't have lip fillers, this trick makes my lips look bigger and more attractive.

To pull off this hack, you'll need a lipliner that is darker than your lipstick. The less transparent your lipstick is, the darker your lipliner shade can be.

First, I overdraw my upper lip, since my natural contour is blurred. 

Next, I exaggerate the natural wrinkles on my lips (think Angelina Jolie). 

Finally, I apply the lipstick all over my lips without pressing too hard so that the lipliner doesn't smudge.

💄 For the perfect combo to achieve this look, try MAC Retro Matte Lipstick in RUBY WOO paired with NYX Suede Lip Liner in CHERRY SKIES.

It's worth noting that both of these reds have a cool undertone, so they look great together and can make your teeth appear whiter.

Красная помада 💄 

Пользуетесь ли вы красной помадой?

В одно время я ходила с красной помадой почти каждый день). Любовь к красному цвету сложилась как-то сама собой, бледная брюнетка, что может лучше подчеркнуть такую внешность. 

Но красный красному рознь и конечно я выбирала те оттенки, которые подойдут именно мне. 
Это красный с некоторым малиновым подтоном, холодный, благородный и конечно безупречно матовый. Никаких глянцев я не терпела (и до сих пор не люблю). 

Я собирала свою коллекцию матовых красных помад и карандашей. Иногда импульсивно скупая все, что понравится, иногда наоборот ходила и вынашивала идею. В итоге я собрала цвета и текстуры, которые меня не подводят никогда. 
Мой любимый красный среди помад это “MAC ruby woo”. Капризная в нанесении, но ее цвет прощает все. Это какой-то светящийся изнутри бархатный дорогой оттенок. Подобного эффекта я не видела ни у одной другой красной помады.

Красная помада это вызов и она не терпит недочетов. Нося ее нужно выглядеть безупречно от макушки до пяток. Но абсолютно для каждой из вас есть ваш идеальный красный, с которым ваши зубы будут белее, губы пухлее, а ваш образ сексуальнее и женственней.

The first product in the Soothe & Hydrate Complete Collection is… the Smoothing Cleanser. 

Tropic’s best-selling product, gentle and effective cleanser is dermatologist-approved for all skin types. Multi-award winner!

HOW TO USE IT?

Apply 2-4 pumps onto your face and neck every morning and evening, treating yourself to a relaxing massage to reset your mind and stimulate your senses. Then, rinse your super soft Bamboo Face Cloth in warm water and use to wipe away any excess cleanser. 

If you’re wearing makeup, apply another 1-2 pumps for a perfectly purified complexion. Finish with a few splashes of cold water and you’re ready for anything! 

🌴 HERO INGREDIENTS?

This product is freshly made in the UK using the most nutritious, sustainably sourced ingredients from across the globe.

🌿 Green tea extract

What can’t this do? Bursting with antioxidants that protect from UV and free radicals, it also boosts skin cell regeneration and balances sebum levels – perfect for those who suffer from breakouts.

🌿 Golden Jojoba Oil 

Restoring the skin so it stays strong and fully functioning, jojoba oil is actually a liquid wax (rather than a traditional oil) which means it’s more like your skin’s own sebum. That’s why it won’t clog pores and makes it suitable for everyone – a real crowd pleaser. 

🌿 Macadamia Oil 

Native to Australia this anti-inflammatory, menthol-scented oil soothes and purifies while providing a zingy aroma, so your head is left as clear as your skin.

To choose a facial mask that will benefit your skin, it's important to consider your skin type and any specific concerns you may have, such as dryness, acne, or fine lines. 

Look for masks that are designed to address these issues and contain ingredients that are known to be effective, such as probiotics, CoQ10, enzymes for rejuvenation, or salicylic acid for acne. Additionally, pay attention to the consistency and texture of the mask - some may be more suited for oily skin or may feel heavy on dry skin. Once you have a few options in mind, try them out and see which works best for your skin. Remember, consistency is key - using a facial mask regularly can help improve the overall health and appearance of your skin.

”Thanks, it’s MAC” has taken over the internet (okay, mainly tiktok) and rightfully so, buuuuut as with ANY lipstick: it’s not for everyone.
The people hyping it up are all pretty, well, pale — as is your’s truly.
.
I’ve tried to tell customers at work over and over that it’s not for everyone. It’s not a universal shade, but when things go viral logic goes out the window. 
Anyway, here are some alternatives to “Thanks, it’s MAC” (in the same “Lustreglass” formula) that will suit different skin tones and undertones. These are all swatched on pale skin with a pink undertone btw.
. 
Go to your nearest MAC counter to try out YOUR shade, not just the latest viral shade. You’ll end up with the most flattering lipstick for you that way, I promise.

Fairy Lights | Limited Edition launched in Paris

Tại phòng trưng bày cao cấp Napoleon thuộc khách sạn The Westin Paris - Vendôme, những thiết kế bay bổng và lãng mạn từ BST phiên bản giới hạn - FAIRY LIGHTS của 21SIX được ra mắt và đón nhận những tình cảm đặc biệt từ giới mộ điệu. 

Khoảnh khắc bay bổng của thiết kế 𝐄𝐒𝐓𝐇𝐄𝐑 𝐃𝐑𝐄𝐒𝐒 giữa một không gian Châu Âu đậm chất nghệ thuật để lại trong team 21SIX những ấn tượng vô cùng sâu sắc. Người mẫu Pháp vô cùng yêu kiều, quyến rũ cùng thiết kế Váy dạ hội được xếp bèo nhún kỳ công phần thân trên, đính kết pha lê lấp lánh phần cup ngực và tay choàng xẻ tà ấn tượng. Kết hợp tinh tế cùng gam màu Bordeaux Red nồng nàn, toát lên tinh thần "nữ hoàng" đầy kiêu hãnh, thiết kế 𝐄𝐒𝐓𝐇𝐄𝐑 𝐃𝐑𝐄𝐒𝐒 tôn vinh vẻ đẹp trường tồn vượt thời gian.

𝐂𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐲𝐥 𝐓𝐮𝐥𝐥𝐞 𝐂𝐚𝐩𝐞 𝐃𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬 | Sắc hồng Rose Quartz ngọt ngào trong không gian đậm chất nghệ thuật tại Paris
Fairy Lights | Limited Edition launched in Paris

Trong khuôn khổ Tuần lễ Thời trang Paris - Paris Fashion Week tháng 3 năm 2023, thương hiệu 21SIX trình làng ấn tượng BST phiên bản giới hạn - FAIRY LIGHTS tại phòng trưng bày cao cấp Napoleon thuộc khách sạn The Westin Paris - Vendôme. Những thiết kế bay bổng và lãng mạn từ câu chuyện của ánh sáng cổ tích và tình yêu hòa quyện trong từng chi tiết đã làm siêu lòng giới mộ điệu tại đây.

Mang đậm dư vị ngọt ngào từ những rung cảm lãng mạn trong những giấc mơ, cô gái bay bổng và tỏa sáng cùng thiết kế Cheryl Dress giữa một không gian mang đậm chất nghệ thuật châu Âu.

Sau hàng giờ miệt mài làm việc của những nghệ nhân lành nghề, thiết kế Váy dạ hội Cheryl Dress là sự kết hợp thăng hoa giữa chất liệu tơ và lưới bồng bềnh, quyến rũ đầy tinh tế. Các điểm chạm được tính toán hoàn hảo trên từng đường nét khi sự tinh giản trong phần thân trên gợi cảm sẽ làm nổi bật phần chân váy xòe kiểu cách kỳ công, tạo nên hiệu ứng uyển chuyển, thu hút mọi ánh nhìn trong từng bước đi của "nàng công chúa" ngọt ngào và lãng mạn.

Fairy Lights | Limited Edition launched in Paris

Tại phòng trưng bày cao cấp Napoleon thuộc khách sạn The Westin Paris - Vendôme, những thiết kế bay bổng và lãng mạn từ BST phiên bản giới hạn - FAIRY LIGHTS của 21SIX được ra mắt và đón nhận những tình cảm đặc biệt từ giới mộ điệu. 

Khoảnh khắc bay bổng của thiết kế 𝐉𝐚𝐧𝐢 𝐃𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬 giữa một không gian Châu Âu đậm chất nghệ thuật để lại trong team 21SIX những ấn tượng vô cùng sâu sắc. Người mẫu Pháp vô cùng yêu kiều, quyến rũ cùng thiết kế Váy dạ hội được xếp bèo lưới lệch vai tinh tế kết hợp với những đường bèo chạy dọc chân váy như những làn sóng mềm mại tôn lên vóc dáng thanh xuân của cô. Kết hợp tinh tế cùng gam màu Very Peri ngọt ngào, biểu trưng cho nguồn năng lượng tích cực, sự lạc quan và tươi vui, thiết kế 𝐉𝐚𝐧𝐢 𝐃𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬 toát lên thần thái sang trọng, quyến rũ mà tinh tế cho bất cứ ai sở hữu.

Self Portrait of a Nice White Lady, 1995

Today In History

Percy Lavon Julian, chemist who held 138 patents and helped create drugs for treating arthritis and glaucoma [cortisone and physostigmine, (1935)] and Aero Foam, used to put out gas/oil fires in World War II, was born in Montgomery, Alabama on this date April 11, 1899. 

Throughout his life he was socially active in groups seeking to advance conditions for African Americans, helping to found the Legal Defense and Educational Fund of Chicago and serving on the boards of several other organizations and universities.

On this day April 11th in Black History: 

1881-Spelman College, an institution sponsored by John D. Rockefeller's family, opened for Negro women in Atlanta, Georgia. It became the "Radcliffe and the Sarah Lawrence of Negro education."

1908-Jane Matilda Bolin was born in Poughkeepsie, New York, was an American attorney and judge. She was the first black woman to graduate from Yale Law School, the first to join the New York City Bar Association and the first to join the New York City Law Department. Bolin became the first black woman to serve as a judge in the United States when she was sworn into the bench of the New York City Domestic Relations Court in 1939. #happyheavenlybirthdayJaneBolin🥳🙏🏽🕊️🎈

1948-Jackie Robinson signs a professional baseball contract and becomes the first black player in the major leagues.

1972-Benjamin L. Hooks, a Memphis lawyer-minister, becomes the first African American named to the Federal Communications Commission.

1997-The new Museum of African American History opens in Detroit.
It is the largest of its kind in the world.

Percy Lavon Julian, chemist who held 138 patents and helped create drugs for treating arthritis and glaucoma [cortisone and physostigmine, (1935)] and Aero Foam, used to put out gas/oil fires in World War II, was born in Montgomery, Alabama on this date April 11, 1899. 

Throughout his life he was socially active in groups seeking to advance conditions for African Americans, helping to found the Legal Defense and Educational Fund of Chicago and serving on the boards of several other organizations and universities.

❤️🖤💚 MAKE B£A€K H!STOR¥ NO M¥STER¥❤️🖤💚 "!N1957, Marlon Green, an Air Force pilot, applied to be a Continental Airlines pilot. Green had applied to other airlines but was rejected each time. When he filled out his application for Continental, he left the “race” box unchecked. Green made it to the final round of interviews but was not hired, even though he had more flight time than the other candidates who were white.

Green filed a complaint with the Colorado Anti-Discrimination Commission, a landmark case that ended up in the United States Supreme Court which ruled in Greens favor and helped dismantle racial discrimination in the American passenger airline industry.

While David Harris was the first Black pilot hired with a major airline, Marlon Green’s fight for the right to be in the flight deck cleared a path for generations of Black pilots to come. In 2010, Continental dedicated a 737 named for Captain Marlon Green. The aircraft, N77518, still flies for United today.

Thank you, Marlon Green for your contributions towards Black History and paving the way for many to follow 🧑🏾‍✈️✈️

Hashtags are a way to categorize content on social media platforms and make it easier for users to find and engage with specific topics. When used strategically, hashtags can increase your content's visibility, reach, and engagement.

✨Events: Hashtags related to particular events or occasions, such as #SuperBowl, #Oscars, or #BlackHistoryMonth.
✨Locations: Hashtags about specific areas, such as #NewYorkCity, #London, or #BeachVacation.
✨Brands: Hashtags on particular brands or products, such as #Nike, #CocaCola, or #Macbook.
✨Niche: Hashtags associated with an industry or topic, such as #Fitness, #Foodie, or #TravelPhotography.
✨Community: Hashtags related to a specific community or group, such as #LGBTQ+, #BlackLivesMatter, or #Feminism.

By using a combination of relevant hashtags from these categories, you can increase the visibility and reach of your social media content to the right audience. It's essential to keep in mind that the perfect hashtags will vary depending on your specific goals, target audience, and social media platform.
